85
00:04:16,135 --> 00:04:20,700
So affordances is this term that is generally considered to come from the world of industrial

86
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:21,080
design.

87
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:26,185
A great book to read about this is this one, The Design of Everyday Things by Don Norman.

88
00:04:28,137 --> 00:04:30,038
And the classic example of affordances in action

89
00:04:30,098 --> 00:04:31,279
is the design of door handles.

90
00:04:32,359 --> 00:04:34,300
So if you look at this photo, you can see two doors.

91
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,441
And the one on the left should be pushed.

92
00:04:36,461 --> 00:04:37,522
The one on the right should be pulled.

93
00:04:38,322 --> 00:04:41,644
And the problem here is that the handles for both of these doors

94
00:04:41,704 --> 00:04:42,284
look the same.

95
00:04:42,964 --> 00:04:44,885
And also, they both look like they should be pulled.

96
00:04:45,445 --> 00:04:48,067
So you can imagine how people will approach the door

97
00:04:48,087 --> 00:04:50,908
on the left and intuitively pull it instead of pushing it

98
00:04:50,968 --> 00:04:52,369
and look like a bit of a fool.

99
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:58,536
So here we can say that the affordances of these door handles on the left are very poorly designed because they're misleading.

100
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:10,132
By contrast, here are some much better door handles where the push panel on the left clearly affords being pushed in a way that kind of contrasts with the one that should be pulled.

101
00:05:11,905 --> 00:05:14,267
And indeed, in this case, the affordances

102
00:05:14,307 --> 00:05:16,448
are so clear and strong that you could remove the text

103
00:05:16,508 --> 00:05:20,011
from these door handles and use them in any country,

104
00:05:20,091 --> 00:05:22,092
and people would just intuitively use them correctly.

105
00:05:22,653 --> 00:05:24,074
And that's the kind of goal of affordances,

106
00:05:24,134 --> 00:05:27,396
is that it's about communicating

107
00:05:27,456 --> 00:05:29,118
how things work intuitively.

108
00:05:29,918 --> 00:05:31,900
We can talk about this as form-conveying function

109
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,521
to use kind of industrial design lingo.

110
00:05:34,901 --> 00:05:37,245
And designing a font as well is a crucial part

111
00:05:37,265 --> 00:05:39,088
of designing anything that is used by people.

112
00:05:39,108 --> 00:05:41,913
And of course, this includes games and level design.

113
00:05:43,496 --> 00:05:45,259
So what kind of a fonts are we talking about

114
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:46,120
when it comes to level design?

